freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: My shot was given in my left arm.  I had pain from my neck to my hip only on the left side.  The discomfort disappeared around 4:30 on today

On the day after my second vaccine I had pain in the same side of my injection from my neck down to my hip which lasted till around 4:30 pm  Today (day 6) I have pain on my right side (opposite side as my injection) my neck down the outer side of my back.  It was very uncomfortable and limited my ability to turn to my right side without pain.  I continued to move through the pain and now around 3:45 the pain is letting up and my range of turning to the right is almost normal.  It is still tender but greatly improved.  The pain was very similar to the pain I had the day after my shot in the left side.
On the right side of my back/under arm rib cage area.  Much improved from yesterday.  Today have full range of motion (ability to twist both left and right)
